The paper proposes a method for combining one-class classifiers using meta-learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also deals with classification and performance measures, which are relevant to "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Computer Vision" (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper uses experiments to evaluate the proposed method, which could fall under "Data Mining" (cs.DM) or "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
